18/06/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Talks on Croatian membership in the EU will start next year, according to EU leaders attending a two-day summit in Brussels. 
They announced Croatia's status as a candidate country on Friday (18 June). 
"We are very satisfied because Croatia is going with us into Europe," said European Commission President Romano Prodi. 
Croatia hopes to join the EU in 2007, together with Bulgaria and Romania. 
Ten countries joined in May, bringing the total to 25. 
(BBC World - 18/06/04)
